	<text_base_description>Exquisitely renovated, this true house-like condo, offers two levels of living and 3 bedrooms 2.5 baths. Situated on a lush tree-lined street in the heart of Pacific Heights it's a short walk to Alta Plaza, Fillmore and Sacramento Streets. The gem of the home is the backyard, by Boxleaf Design, accessed through French doors off the eat-in kitchen. Complete with a fountain, firepit, and verdant landscaping, the garden setting offers a tranquil balance of indoor/outdoor California living. The recently renovated interior showcases designer touches mixed with Victorian details, including dramatic ceiling heights, Elitis wallpaper, calcatta, and carrara marble, Waterworks fixtures, Sub Zero and Thermador appliances, built-in Miele coffee machine, and a walk-in temperature controlled wine cellar capable of holding 500 bottles.  </text_base_description>
